main event: An unidentified aircraft was detected by radar in Key West, Florida on May 9, 1952, traveling at high speeds.
interesting points: The radar operators reported the object was traveling at 4800 mph., The object was observed at an altitude of 35,000 feet., The initial sighting involved radar contact with a subsequent similar contact the following day., There was no further information or visual confirmation of the object., This report is part of the historical Project Blue Book, which investigated UFO sightings.
witness description: no specific witnesses mentioned as the sighting was detected via radar
